The Philadelphia 76ers are 8-1 since trading James Harden for role players, while the L.A. Clippers are 0-4 with Harden.

The 76ers have the best record in the NBA, while the Clippers are 12th in the West.

Xem th√™m Philly has already beaten the championship-favorite Boston Celtics, while LAC has already lost to the league-worst Memphis Grizzlies.

When Harden‚Äôs on the court, the Clippers‚Äô defense ranks last in the league. It was the same for the 76ers last season when Harden played, but this season they have a top 5 defense without him.

Philly has a top 5 offense this season, while LA‚Äôs 104.3 PPG since the Harden trade ranks them dead last in the NBA.

And just to top it off, Harden is averaging 13.5 PPG and 4.3 APG in LA, while Tyrese Maxey is blossoming into the superstar Harden was meant to be in Philly, with 28.6 PPG on the season and a 50-piece tonight.

Whichever way you slice it, so far this trade has been a godsend for the 76ers and a disaster for the Clippers.
